./sdp/logs/Lead_frac-0003_1777699485.log:19874:- Added the CypherClaw narrative API regression suite plus a minimal auth gate (T-005@20260502T001347Z): `cypherclaw.narrative_api.create_app(...)` now accepts an optional `auth_token` keyword that, when set, requires every endpoint to carry a matching `X-Narrative-Auth` header (missing/wrong → 401); empty/unset preserves the existing auth-disabled behavior so T-010's env-var pull and startup warning land cleanly. `tests/test_narrative_api_memory.py` and `tests/test_narrative_api_events.py` now pin the four scenario floors (success path, auth failure when enabled, bad input validation, downstream-engine error handling) for `POST /memory/search`, `GET /events`, and `POST /events`, plus 503 fallback behavior when the deploy-side `cypherclaw.narrative.{memory,events}` package is absent and append-returns-None record synthesis. `pytest --cov=cypherclaw.narrative_api` reports 84% module coverage.
./sdp/logs/Lead_frac-0003_1777699485.log:19914:- Added `docs/cypherclaw-sampler-architecture.md` to fill the gap between the sampler PRD and the musicianship roadmap: it lists the landed sampler components (`sample_capture_daemon.py`, `sample_capture_verify.py`, `sampler_buffers.py`, `sampler_dispatch.py`, `synthesis/sampler_effects.scd`, `render/antipatterns.py`), traces the end-to-end signal flow from JACK input through capture, tagging, `index.sqlite`, dispatch, the `sw_sampler_fx` bus, and the master bus, names both live anti-pattern detectors (`sampler_dominating`, `sampler_silent_quintet_member`), enumerates integration seams (identity, cast planner, mix engine, composer, operator diagnostics), and explicitly flags `SampleLibrary`, `SampleSelector`, `sw_sampler.scd`, and quintet identity convergence as still pending; `tests/test_cypherclaw_sampler_architecture.py` pins the doc's required sections, the referenced file paths, and the live anti-pattern names so future renames or section drops force the doc to update with the code.
./sdp/logs/Lead_frac-0003_1777699485.log:19915:- Updated `docs/cypherclaw-musicianship-roadmap.md` to describe the active quintet direction: `sw_bell_warm`, `sw_bowed`, `sw_breath`, `sw_pad`, and the new `sw_sampler` memory voice; the roadmap now separates landed sampler modules (`sample_capture_daemon.py`, `sampler_buffers.py`, `sampler_dispatch.py`, `sampler_effects.scd`, anti-pattern checks) from still-pending identity/library/SynthDef convergence so the documentation matches the tree's real partial-rollout state.
./sdp/logs/Lead_frac-0003_1777699485.log:19924:- Added executable production-course curriculum exercises: `ExerciseSpec` now carries a runnable `template` and explicit `expected_features` while preserving the legacy `expected` alias; generated exercise specs include both metadata forms; and the EMSD curriculum now has verifier-backed exercises for intervals/scales, chord voicings, progressions, rhythm/groove, counterpoint, synthesis architecture, mix/master, SenseWeave mapping, Theramini ensemble, genre strategy, and full-arc production.
./sdp/logs/Lead_frac-0003_1777699485.log:19925:- Added course-driven self-critique and revision targets: `self_critique.py` now maps production-course chapter concepts (mode_scale, harmonic_function, meter_groove, counterpoint_relation, synthesis_architecture, mix_role, spatial_intent, genre_strategy, transition_type, phase_profile) to concrete ear-engine metric thresholds via `COURSE_METRIC_MAP`; `thresholds_for_course()` merges per-section course metadata into quality thresholds (stricter wins); `critique_score_with_course()` returns a `CourseCritiqueReport` with `CourseFailure` attribution naming the specific course concept behind each metric violation; `revision_targets_from_failures()` maps failures to `RevisionTargets` specifying which musical dimensions (form, harmony, rhythm, register, mix, strategy) are open for bounded revision without changing piece identity; `revise_score()` accepts an optional `course` kwarg; `tracker_compiler.py` and `duet_composer.py` fallback paths now pass section production_course to `revise_score`.
./sdp/logs/Lead_frac-0003_1777699485.log:19930:- Added artistic identity portfolio reporting and surface snapshots: new `portfolio_report.py` module provides `derive_portfolio_report()` for comprehensive identity summaries from repertoire metrics, preferred forms/modes, motif counts, practice block coverage with EMSD course codes, growth-state keys, and ear quality averages; and `derive_surface_snapshot()` for face/operator display data (current song title, section caption, practice block, artistic-intent line). Graceful degradation handles empty repertoire, missing fields, corrupt score trees, and absent growth state without hallucinating data.
./sdp/logs/Lead_frac-0003_1777699485.log:19933:- Added pre-performance self-critique and bounded revision passes: new `self_critique.py` module provides `preview_score()` for offline metric analysis, `critique_score()` for threshold-based quality gating, and `revise_score()` for one bounded rewrite attempt that preserves piece identity (key, mood, tempo) while improving at least one failed metric.
./sdp/logs/Lead_frac-0003_1777699485.log:19944:- Added section-level motif development and local harmonic progressions: `tracker_compiler.py` now labels each section as statement, sequence/fragment, contrast inversion, recall answer, liquidation, or residue, reshapes phrase material accordingly, and applies section-local progressions that are exposed on tracker scenes and steps for bass/progression verification.
./sdp/logs/Lead_frac-0003_1777699485.log:19946:- Fixed recalled motif rhythm metadata so later sections that borrow earlier material inherit the current scene's rhythm/progression profile instead of leaking the source scene's old `rhythm_development`.
